---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Deployment | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>Deployment</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard is intended for controlled enterprise environments where governance
      is part of production operations, not a later add-on.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Placement and Intent</h2>
    <p>
      The platform belongs in the runtime path between application services and AI/model
      endpoints. This ensures every authorization-sensitive interaction is governed before
      the request reaches or consumes model outputs.
    </p>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is designed to support environments with strict audit posture and
      operational controls.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deployment Model</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Independent service execution with explicit trust boundaries.</li>
      <li>Signed policy artifacts with controlled promotion flows.</li>
      <li>Clear environment separation for policy, keys, and execution tiers.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Trust Boundaries and Operational Posture</h2>
    <p>
      Policy is authoritative at enforcement time.
      Applications and downstream systems should not silently bypass governance outcomes.
      When policy material is missing or unverifiable, decisions must fail closed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Decision Boundary Pattern</h2>
    <div class="flow-diagram">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Policy boundary</p>
        <p>Control points prevent unauthorised model execution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Fail-closed behavior</p>
        <p>Unverifiable states block unsafe execution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Deployment evidence</p>
        <p>Operational evidence supports assurance reviews.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Integration Pattern</h2>
    <p>
      Treat BeaconGuard as an authorization layer with explicit request normalization and
      deterministic enforcement responses. This reduces application coupling and keeps
      governance policy lifecycle separate from model integration details.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Technical references</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/deployment-integration">Deployment and integration</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/compliance-audit">Compliance controls</a></li>
      <li><a href="/how-it-works">How BeaconGuard enforces decisions</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/trust-assurance">Understand trust boundaries</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Discuss deployment needs</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
